Question 2

By looking at the number of cases per capita, some states appear to do better than others compared to the raw data. The peak in the CA plot appears much smaller, while the peak in the LA plot appears much larger because CAs population is much larger. So while CA has more cases than LA, they have a smaller ratio to the total population.
